{"annotations": [{"id": ["mesh:D005355"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Fibrosis", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9998656511306763, "span": {"begin": 0, "end": 8}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1281"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "collagen type I and III", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9963920712471008, "span": {"begin": 107, "end": 130}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2335"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "fibronectin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9940891265869141, "span": {"begin": 132, "end": 143}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002921"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "scarring", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9965607523918152, "span": {"begin": 262, "end": 270}}, {"id": ["mesh:D010900"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "functional impairment", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9761018753051758, "span": {"begin": 283, "end": 304}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002908"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "chronic inflammation", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9839317798614502, "span": {"begin": 365, "end": 385}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ECM-producing cells", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.8238198757171631, "span": {"begin": 434, "end": 453}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "myofibroblasts", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8192797303199768, "span": {"begin": 466, "end": 480}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "activated stellate cells", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8484989404678345, "span": {"begin": 482, "end": 506}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "fibroblasts", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8526462912559509, "span": {"begin": 508, "end": 519}}, {"id": ["mesh:D007249"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "inflammation", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9965641498565674, "span": {"begin": 710, "end": 722}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000860"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "hypoxia", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9730687737464905, "span": {"begin": 724, "end": 731}}, {"id": ["mesh:D005355"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "fibrosis", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.999935507774353, "span": {"begin": 801, "end": 809}}], "text": "Fibrosis is the&nbsp;pathological consequence&nbsp;of excessive ECM deposition, primarily composed of&nbsp;collagen type I and III, fibronectin, and glycosaminoglycans. When ECM production exceeds its degradation, tissues undergo&nbsp;progressive stiffening and scarring, leading to functional impairment of affected organs. This process occurs in response to&nbsp;chronic inflammation, mechanical stress, and prolonged injury, where ECM-producing cells (e.g.,&nbsp;myofibroblasts, activated stellate cells, fibroblasts) become&nbsp;overactive&nbsp;and produce an excessive matrix. The excessive ECM deposition disrupts normal tissue architecture, interferes with cellular signaling, and promotes further&nbsp;inflammation, hypoxia, and cell death, establishing a&nbsp;self-perpetuating cycle&nbsp;of fibrosis progression (PMID: 24265236).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:32:20 +0000 2026"}